# HTML / CSS / JS Coding Standards

These rules apply to every `.html` file and all CSS/JS under `assets/`.

## Document structure
- Use the HTML5 doctype: `<!doctype html>`.
- The `<html>` element MUST have `lang="en"`.
- The `<head>` MUST declare `<meta charset="UTF-8">` first, followed by
  `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">`.

## Headings
- Exactly **one `<h1>` per page**.
- Heading levels MUST NOT skip (never jump `h1` -> `h3`). Nest in order.

## Images
Every `<img>` MUST include:
- `alt` (descriptive for content images, `alt=""` for decorative ones)
- explicit `width` and `height` attributes (to prevent layout shift)
- `loading="lazy"`
- `decoding="async"`

Above-the-fold hero/LCP images may use `loading="eager"` with a comment
explaining why.

## Links
- All external `<a>` tags MUST use `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`.
- Internal links use relative paths (e.g. `./about.html`).

## Scripts & styles
- JavaScript is loaded at the end of `<body>` with the `defer` attribute,
  or via `type="module"`. Never use blocking inline scripts.
- CSS is loaded in `<head>` via `<link rel="stylesheet">`.
- **No inline styles** (`style="..."`). All styling lives in `assets/css/`.
- **No inline event handlers** (`onclick=""`, etc.). Wire all behavior with
  `addEventListener` in `assets/js/`.

## Semantic HTML
- Use semantic elements where they fit: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`,
  `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`.
- Do NOT use a `<div>` where a semantic element is appropriate.

## Required on every page
- Skip-to-content link as the first focusable element.
- `<meta name="description">`.
- Open Graph: `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`.
- `<link rel="canonical">`.

## Style conventions
- Two-space indentation in HTML/CSS/JS.
- Class names use kebab-case; BEM-ish (`block__element`, `block--modifier`).
- Prefer CSS custom properties (tokens) over hard-coded values.
